BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:j7oN_jFABv-JOv52pzkFc
SUMMARY:Highway 9 Bridge Planting Party
DTSTAMP:20260307T235948Z
DTSTART:20260307T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description Join us at this restoration site along South Skagit
	 Highway near the Highway 9 bridge. From 9am-12pm we'll plant native trees
	 and shrubs to restore riparian habitat at this riverside site. These plan
	ts will help restore the Skagit River and improve habitat for salmon and m
	any other animals. Bring a club\, group and all your friends- all ages wel
	come! Please dress for the weather\, and wear shoes that can get muddy. We
	'll provide gloves\, tools and hot drinks/snacks!  Click the link to regis
	ter today!\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/highway-9-brid
	ge-planting-party/18264975/2026-03-07T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdo
	ors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/highway-9-bridge-planting
	-party/18264975/2026-03-07T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:toplwgWUYdxE4tcjnoXSe
SUMMARY:Journaling the Garden
DTSTAMP:20260307T235948Z
DTSTART:20260307T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Nature journaling at the Bellevue Botanical Garden is a wonderf
	ul way to connect with the environment through curiosity and observation o
	f the natural world. This free adult program will help guide your practice
	 whether you are just starting out or are an experienced journaler. In thi
	s warm and welcoming environment\, you will be encouraged to experiment an
	d find your voice. In each session we will gather for introductions and br
	ief guidance\, and then head out into Garden to journal and come back toge
	ther to share experiences.   \n\nPlease bring a dedicated journal and some
	thing to write with. We will meet at 9am the first Saturday of January-Nov
	ember 2026. Registration is recommended but not required. REGISTER NOW.  \
	n\nThis free adult program is facilitated by Anne Dziok\, Adult Education 
	Program Manager. Anne is a practicing multi-media artist who shows her wor
	k regionally.    \n\nEmail us  with questions.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity
	.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/17658183/2026-03-07T00\n\nFrom
	 SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/176
	58183/2026-03-07T00
LOCATION:Sharp Cabin\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
